{
  "texts": [
    "Such systems are not common, but nevertheless it is helpful to discuss why model-independent source reconstruction works.",
    "Let us think of the six components on the source as being one reference β 0 and five β vectors.",
    "These β are magnified and sheared into five sets of five observable θ vectors each by five different magnification matrices.",
    "The original β vectors are unknown (5 × 2 numbers, because we are in 2D).",
    "The five magnification matrices are also unknown (3 × 5 numbers, because magnification matrices are symmetric and have 3 independent components)."
  ]
}